Haiku Atlas CLI Reference
=========================

Functional reference for the Haiku Atlas command line tools.

Tools
-----

- atlas-indexer: builds or updates an Atlas SQLite index.
- atlas-query: reads an Atlas SQLite index.

Common Option
-------------

--db PATH

SQLite index path.

Default:

    data/haiku-atlas.sqlite3

atlas-indexer
-------------

    atlas-indexer [--db PATH] [--full | --incremental] [--sdk PATH | --haiku-source PATH | PATH]
    atlas-indexer help

Verbs / Modes

--full

Force known headers to be reindexed.

--incremental

Index new/changed headers, remove deleted headers, keep unchanged headers.

No mode:

    atlas-indexer --db data/haiku-atlas.sqlite3

Initialize the database only.

Inputs

--sdk /boot/system/develop/headers

Use an installed Haiku SDK header root.

--haiku-source /boot/home/haiku

Use a Haiku source checkout. Currently scans:

    /boot/home/haiku/headers

    atlas-indexer /path/to/headers

Use a header root directly.

Examples

    atlas-indexer --db data/haiku-atlas.sqlite3 --sdk /boot/system/develop/headers

    atlas-indexer --db data/haiku-atlas.sqlite3 --full --haiku-source /boot/home/haiku

    atlas-indexer --db /tmp/atlas.sqlite3 --incremental tests/fixtures/simple_api

Output

    atlas-indexer: incremental scanned=1 new=1 changed=0 deleted=0 unchanged=0 db=/tmp/atlas.sqlite3 source=tests/fixtures/simple_api

Fields:

- scanned: header files found.
- new: files inserted into the index.
- changed: files reindexed.
- deleted: files removed from the index.
- unchanged: files reused from cache.

atlas-query
-----------

    atlas-query [--db PATH] COMMAND

search

    atlas-query --db data/haiku-atlas.sqlite3 search BView

Search symbols by name.

Output:

    class	BView	View.h:1
    method	BView::Draw	View.h:3

Columns:

    kind	qualified_name	location

show

    atlas-query --db data/haiku-atlas.sqlite3 show BView

Show one symbol.

Output:

    BView
    Kind: class
    Qualified: BView
    Header: View.h:1
    Declaration: class BView : public BHandler {
    Relations:
      contains: BView::BView
      contains: BView::Draw
      defined_in: View.h
      inherits: BHandler

help

    atlas-query help

Print this reference.

dump-symbols

    atlas-query --db data/haiku-atlas.sqlite3 dump-symbols

Print all indexed symbols.

Output:

    class	BView
    constructor	BView::BView
    method	BView::Draw
    enum	orientation
    struct	rgb_color

Columns:

    kind	qualified_name

dump-kits

    atlas-query --db data/haiku-atlas.sqlite3 dump-kits

Print indexed kits.

Output:

    name	display_name

Currently empty until kit detection is implemented.

Exit Codes
----------

- 0: command completed.
- 1: atlas-query show did not find the requested symbol.
